06. Plot Treemap with NHSÔÉÅ

This example displays a Treemap using a portion of the NHS dataset. This example needs pyAMR to load the corresponding data.

Warning

It is not completed!

Warning

It might take some time to load.

Note

It uses plotly.express rather than go.Treemap.

Note

https://plotly.com/python/treemaps/

 16 import numpy as np
 17 import pandas as pd
 18 import plotly.express as px
 19
 20 from plotly.io import show
 21
 22 # Import own libraries
 23 from pyamr.core.sari import sari
 24 from pyamr.datasets.load import load_data_nhs
 25
 26 try:
 27     __file__
 28     TERMINAL = True
 29 except:
 30     TERMINAL = False
 31
 32
 33 # Methods
 34 def build_hierarchical_dataframe(df, levels, value_column, color_columns=None):
 35     """
 36     Build a hierarchy of levels for Sunburst or Treemap charts.
 37
 38     Levels are given starting from the bottom to the top of the hierarchy,
 39     ie the last level corresponds to the root.
 40     """
 41     df_all_trees = pd.DataFrame(columns=['id', 'parent', 'value', 'color'])
 42     for i, level in enumerate(levels):
 43         df_tree = pd.DataFrame(columns=['id', 'parent', 'value', 'color'])
 44         dfg = df.groupby(levels[i:]).sum()
 45         dfg = dfg.reset_index()
 46         df_tree['id'] = dfg[level].copy()
 47         if i < len(levels) - 1:
 48             df_tree['parent'] = dfg[levels[i+1]].copy()
 49         else:
 50             df_tree['parent'] = 'total'
 51         df_tree['value'] = dfg[value_column]
 52         df_tree['color'] = dfg[color_columns[0]]
 53         df_all_trees = df_all_trees.append(df_tree, ignore_index=True)
 54     total = pd.Series(dict(id='total', parent='',
 55         value=df[value_column].sum(),
 56         color=df[color_columns[0]].sum()))
 57     df_all_trees = df_all_trees.append(total, ignore_index=True)
 58     return df_all_trees
 59
 60
 61 TERMINAL = True
 62
 63 # --------------------------------------------------------------------
 64 #                               Main
 65 # --------------------------------------------------------------------
 66 # Load data
 67 data, antimicrobials, microorganisms = load_data_nhs(nrows=10000)
 68
 69 # Create DataFrame
 70 dataframe = data.groupby(['specimen_code',
 71                           'microorganism_code',
 72                           'antimicrobial_code',
 73                           'sensitivity']) \
 74                 .size().unstack().fillna(0)
 75
 76 # Compute frequency
 77 dataframe['freq'] = dataframe.sum(axis=1)
 78
 79 # Compute sari
 80 dataframe['sari'] = sari(dataframe, strategy='hard')
 81 dataframe['sari_medium'] = sari(dataframe, strategy='medium')
 82 dataframe['sari_soft'] = sari(dataframe, strategy='soft')
 83
 84 # Reset index
 85 dataframe = dataframe.reset_index()
 86
 87 # --------------------------------------------
 88 # Add info for popup
 89 # --------------------------------------------
 90 dataframe = dataframe.merge(antimicrobials,
 91     how='left', left_on='antimicrobial_code',
 92     right_on='antimicrobial_code')
 93
 94 # Add antimicrobials information
 95 dataframe = dataframe.merge(microorganisms,
 96     how='left', left_on='microorganism_code',
 97     right_on='microorganism_code')
 98
 99 # Format dataframe
100 dataframe = dataframe.round(decimals=3)
101
102 # Replace
103 dataframe.microorganism_name = \
104     dataframe.microorganism_name.str.title()
105 dataframe.columns = \
106     dataframe.columns.str.title().str.replace('_', ' ')
107
108
109 # Show
110 if TERMINAL:
111     print("\nColumns:")
112     print(dataframe.dtypes)
113     print("\nDF:")
114     print(dataframe)
115
116
117 # -------------------------------------------
118 # Plot
119 # -------------------------------------------
120 def guide_template(names):
121     return '<br>'.join([
122         "%2d <b>%-45s</b> %%{customdata[%s]}" % (i, n, i )
123             for i, n in enumerate(names)])
124
125 # Guide template
126 htmp_guide = guide_template(dataframe.columns.tolist())
127
128 # Define own template
129 htmp = "Specimen:      (%{customdata[0]})<br>"
130 htmp+= "Microorganism: %{customdata[26]} (%{customdata[1]})<br>"
131 htmp+= "Antimicrobial: %{customdata[12]} (%{customdata[2]})<br>"
132 htmp+= "Freq: %{customdata[8]}<br>"
133 htmp+= "SARI: %{customdata[9]}<br>"
134
135 htmp = "(%{customdata[0]})<br>"
136 htmp+= "%{customdata[26]} (%{customdata[1]})<br>"
137 htmp+= "%{customdata[12]} (%{customdata[2]})<br>"
138 htmp+= "Freq: %{customdata[8]}<br>"
139 htmp+= "SARI: %{customdata[9]}<br>"
140
141 # Display
142 fig = px.treemap(dataframe,
143     path=['Specimen Code',
144           'Microorganism Code',
145           'Antimicrobial Code'],
146     #hover_name=,
147     hover_data=dataframe.columns.tolist(),
148     values='Freq',
149     color='Sari',
150     color_continuous_scale='Reds',
151     title='Treemap of <Microorganisms, Antimicrobials> pairs')
152
153
154 # Show current template
155 print(fig.data[0].hovertemplate)
156
157 """
158 The default hover template looks as follows:
159
160     labels=%{label}<br>
161     Freq=%{value}<br>
162     parent=%{parent}<br>
163     id=%{id}<br>
164     Microorganism Name=%{customdata[0]}<br>
165     Name=%{customdata[1]}<br>
166     Sari Medium=%{customdata[2]}<br>
167     Sari Soft=%{customdata[3]}<br>
168     Sari=%{color}
169     <extra></extra>
170 """
171

191 fig.update_layout(
192     margin={
193         'l': 0,
194         'r': 0,
195         'b': 0,
196         't': 0,
197         'pad': 4
198      })
199 # ----------------------------
200 # Save
201 # ----------------------------
202 # Libraries
203 import time
204 from pathlib import Path
205
206 # Define pipeline path
207 path = Path('./objects') / 'plot_main08_treemap'
208 filename = '%s.html' % time.strftime("%Y%m%d-%H%M%S")
209
210 # Create folder (if it does not exist)
211 path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
212
213 # Save
214 fig.write_html("%s/%s" % (path, filename))
215
216 # Show
217 show(fig)
